hpnicfDot11Sa.name: hpnicfDot11Sa

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11Sa.description: This MIB module provides spectrum analysis information. The initial revision of this MIB module. The spectrum analysis module on APs is able to examine the radio frequency (RF) environment in which the Wi-Fi network is operating, identify interference and classify its sources. An analysis of the results can then be used to quickly isolate issues with packet transmission, channel quality, and traffic congestion caused by contention with other devices operating in the same band or channel.

hpnicfDot11SaCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11SaCfgTable
hpnicfDot11SaCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure spectrum analysis.

hpnicfDot11SaCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11SaCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11SaCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the spectrum analysis configuration.

hpnicfDot11SaCfgRadioType.name: hpnicfDot11SaCfgRadioType
hpnicfDot11SaCfgRadioType.description: Represents the radio type of the configuration.

hpnicfDot11SaEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SaEnable
hpnicfDot11SaEnable.description: Represents whether spectrum analysis is enabled globally.

hpnicfDot11SaRptDevType.name: hpnicfDot11SaRptDevType
hpnicfDot11SaRptDevType.description: Represents which types of interference devices should be reported.

hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevEnable
hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevEnable.description: Represents whether the interference device trap is enabled.

hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevType.name: hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevType
hpnicfDot11SaTrapDevType.description: Represents which types of interference device will send traps when the interference device trap is enabled.

hpnicfDot11SaTrapAQEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SaTrapAQEnable

hpnicfDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11SaTrapAQThreshold
hpnicfDot11SaTrapAQThreshold.description: Represents the air quality trap threshold. When the air quality is below this value, the air quality trap will be sent.

hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable
hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMEnable.description: Configure whether to trigger RRM to run when an access point detects a certain level of interference.

hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.name: hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt
hpnicfDot11SaDrivenRRMSnt.description: Configure the threshold at which RRM will be triggered. When the interference level for the access point rises above the threshold level, RRM initiates a local dynamic channel assignment (DCA) run and changes the channel of the affected access point radio if possible to improve network performance. Low represents a decreased sensitivity to changes in the environment while high represents an increased sensitivity.

hpnicfDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.name: hpnicfDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry
hpnicfDot11SaRtFFTDataEntry.description: This entry contains the real-time FFT data for spectrum analysis.
